While we've been in the comfort of our homes over the past two years, it’s time to step out and explore with our little ones ensuring a safe environment for them. 
@dlfavenue has proven to be a destination that follows safety protocols rigorously while shopping & enjoying with Videh, making it a fun-filled experience.

The 2nd floor at @dlfavenue is the gateway to a child's paradise! From our favourite brands like @rookieusa.in , @hamleys_india , @bouncefitness_saket to snacking at @chai_point and @popcornandcoindia , you have it all on the 2nd floor!

DLF Avenue, Saket follows utmost safety precautions, from thermal screening and sanitisation at the entrance to the installation of HEPA filtration system in the premises.
It was reassuring to see Covid marshals throughout the place to keep a check on the mask and social distancing being followed strictly.

We had a wonderful time at @dlfavenue !
When are you planning a visit?!

Winter season calls for an extra boost of hydration for the skin, especially if you are dry skin babies like Videh and his mommy!
And the one that I trust the most for my baby’s skin is @curatiobaby Atogla cream and lotion.
.

Atogla contains Ceramide, Cholesterol and anti irritant complex that help in building the skin barrier and provide intense moisturization. Atogla protects the skin from dryness and scaling in the winters.

I strongly recommend Atogla lotion as it's a good moisturizer and Atogla cream if your baby has extra dry skin.

The only makeup routine I know😅
Products and details:

1. Moisturised my face with @cetaphil_india 
2. Applied lip balm from @mynykaa 
3. Illuminating primer from @kaybykatrina 
4. Peach corrector from @kaybykatrina (works perfectly for fair skin tone, no need for concealer) blend blend!
5. Mix @reachedmars BB cream (oh! God I love it!) with @lakmeindia Lumi cream for hydrating medium coverage. Blend blend!
6. Set undereye with @paccosmetic translucent powder
7. Random colour on eyelids (beacause I don’t know the A of eye makeup🙈) Using palette from @makeuprevolutionindia 
8. Favourite eyeliner from @lovecolorbar (sketch pen tip in liquid liner)
9. Kajal from @nykaacosmetics smudged with a brush so it does not smudge later!
10. Long lasting liquid blush from @reneeofficial 
11. Setting liquid blush with earthy toned powder blush from @maccosmeticsindia ( a light brush all over the face gives a nice flushed look.
12. Mascara from @lorealparis 
13. Highlighter from @officialswissbeauty 
14. Also highlighted inner corners of the eyes, make a big difference 
15. Setting/glow spray from @suroskiebeauty Ooooh! I love it!
16. Lipstick of your choice please, I am not very much of a lipstick person!

Hoping I have explained everything in detail. 
Any queries, let me know !

.
.
.
